<TITLE> Ex-national cricketer Opee, former wife arrested </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 7 (bdnews24.com)  Police early Friday arrested former national cricketer Mehrab Hossain Opee in a woman repression case filed by his former wife, who was detained later. Bangladesh's first one-day century maker was picked from near his house at 99 Aga Sadek Road under Kotwali Police Station at 2am, sub-inspector Fakhrul Alam told bdnews24.com. The Women and Children Repression Prevention Special Tribunal Court-4 issued an arrest warrant after Opee's former wife Radiya Hossain Runy filed the case. Police produced Opee before a court at around midday and the court ordered him into jail. Jailer of Dhaka Central Jail Shafiqul Islam told bdnews24.com in the evening Opee and his former wife were received at the jail gate at 6:45pm. Ramna police later arrested Runy in connection with a fraud case. Ramna Police Station sub-inspector Kalpana Rani Datta said Runy was arrested on charges of fraud and embezzlement brought by Ahsanur Rahman Arju Thursday. In his case, Arju alleged that Runy had borrowed Tk 4.25 lakh from him but did not repay the loan. A court also sent Runy into jail. bdnews
